data.title: FB: Kennesaw State Inaugural Home Football Game to Air on Atlanta's CW69
data.meta_description: Kennesaw State University Athletics and WUPA-TV (Atlanta's CW69) today announced a partnership to televise the Owls' inaugural home football game against Edward
data.text:
Home Opener Versus Edward Waters to Start at 4 P.M.

Official Release (PDF) | Schedule | Tickets

KENNESAW, Ga. (June 2, 2015) â€“ Kennesaw State University Athletics and WUPA-TV (Atlanta's CW69) today announced a partnership to televise the Owls' inaugural home football game against Edward Waters on Sept. 12 at Fifth Third Bank Stadium. Kickoff for the historic game is 4 p.m.

"We are extremely excited and grateful to join forces with CW69 to televise the inaugural Kennesaw State home football game," KSU Director of Athletics Vaughn Williams said. "The airing of this historic game on CW69 is a tremendous opportunity to showcase Kennesaw State University and Owl Athletics to the greater Atlanta community."

WUPA Station Manager Tim Bennett commented "CW69 is proud to telecast the first home football game for the Kennesaw State Owls. In a market that is thirsty for live local sports, we feel this once in a lifetime event will be a big draw for local viewers and college football fans in the Atlanta area."

Over the course of the last two years, CW69 has committed itself to more sports programming by partnering with the Atlanta Falcons to televise preseason games, airing two hours of weekly team programming and producing a regular slate of Falcons specials each year.

CW69 is also a network affiliate for Atlantic Coast Conference (ACC) football. An ACC game will precede the Kennesaw State-Edward Waters game.

Fans still have the opportunity to witness history in person as a limited number of season tickets remain available. For further information and to purchase tickets, please call (470) 578-6957.

Kennesaw State, which plays at the NCAA Division I Football Championship Subdivision (FCS) level and is a member of the Big South Conference, opens its debut season on Sept. 3 when it plays East Tennessee State in Johnson City, Tenn.

WUPA-TV (CW69), which is owned by CBS, is an over-the-air broadcast station available through all cable providers in addition to Direct TV and other satellite customers. It airs on 810 on Comcast, 1069 on U-Verse, 709 on Charter, 69 on DirecTV and 6376 on DISH TV.

ABOUT KENNESAW STATE ATHLETICS: Kennesaw State University sponsors 18 intercollegiate athletic sports and competes at the NCAA Division I level. Seventeen Owls teams compete in the Atlantic Sun Conference. Football will play at the NCAA Division I Football Championship Series (FCS )level and compete as an associate member of the Big South Conference beginning in 2015. KSU has won a total of six national championships at the NAIA and NCAA Division II levels. Kennesaw State became an NCAA Division I member prior to the 2005-06 athletics season.

ABOUT KENNESAW STATE UNIVERSITY: Kennesaw State University is the third-largest university in Georgia, offering 80 graduate and undergraduate degrees, including doctorates in education, business and nursing, and a new Ph.D. in international conflict management. A member of the 30-unit University System of Georgia, Kennesaw State is a comprehensive, residential institution with a growing population of 24,629 students from more than 130 countries.

To keep up with the latest Kennesaw State athletics news follow the Owls on Twitter @KSUOwlNation or by liking Kennesaw State University on Facebook.
